original_font_information.description: Fell Types - French Canon size - Italic. Typeface from the  types bequeathed in 1686 to the University of Oxford by John Fell. Originally cut by Peter De Walpergen. Acquisition in 1686. To be printed at 39 points to match the original size. Autospaced and autokerned using iKern developed by Igino Marini.
